' ─── Inheritance hierarchy ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

UnlockableContent <|-- Block
Block <|-- Floor
Floor <|-- OverlayFloor
OverlayFloor <|-- OreBlock

' ─── Interface implementations ───────────────────────────────────────────────

Block ..|> Senseable
Tile ..|> Position
Tile ..|> QuadTreeObject
Tile ..|> Displayable
Tiles ..|> IterableTile

' ─── Composition / Aggregation relationships ─────────────────────────────────

World *-- Tiles : "tiles\n(canonical grid)"

Tiles *-- Tile : "array[width*height]\n(row-major: y*width+x)"

Tile *-- Block  : "block\n(wall / structure layer)"
Tile *-- Floor  : "floor\n(base terrain layer)"
Tile *-- Floor  : "overlay\n(ore / scorch layer)"
Tile o-- "0..1" Building : "build\n(nullable entity)"

Floor o-- Block : "blendGroup\n(self or peer)"
Floor o-- Block : "wall variant"
Floor o-- Block : "decoration variant"

note bottom of Tile
  Three independent layers per tile:
  1. floor  — base terrain, drawn first
  2. overlay — OverlayFloor drawn on top
  3. block   — wall/structure placed on tile

  Multiblock (size > 1): center tile owns
  the Building; satellite tiles share refs.

  Events fired: TileChangeEvent,
  TilePreChangeEvent, TileFloorChangeEvent,
  TileOverlayChangeEvent
end note

note right of Tiles
  Flat 1D array — no chunk-based storage.
  Access: get(x,y) → array[y*width+x]
  World.tile(x,y) delegates to tiles.get(x,y)
end note

@enduml
